%I A309409 #13 May 24 2026 19:10:39
%S A309409 5,7,2707,163193
%N A309409 Numbers k such that (37^k + 1)/38 is prime.
%C A309409 Larger terms correspond to probable primes.
%H A309409 P. Bourdelais, <a href="https://listserv.nodak.edu/cgi-bin/wa.exe?A2=NMBRTHRY;417ab0d6.0906">A Generalized Repunit Conjecture</a>.
%H A309409 OEIS Wiki, <a href="https://oeis.org/wiki/Primes_of_the_form_(a%5En%2Bb%5En)/(a%2Bb)_and_(a%5En-b%5En)/(a-b)">Primes of the form (a^n+b^n)/(a+b) and (a^n-b^n)/(a-b)</a>.
%t A309409 Do[p=Prime[n]; If[PrimeQ[(37^p + 1)/38], Print[p]], {n, 1, 1000000}]
%o A309409 (PARI) is(n)=ispseudoprime((37^n+1)/38)
%K A309409 nonn,hard,more,changed
%O A309409 1,1
%A A309409 _Paul Bourdelais_, Jul 29 2019
